(Netcare911 via Twitter) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Eight men were injured, six of them seriously, when a wall collapsed on them in Kowie Road, Boskruin, Randburg, on Saturday morning, paramedics said.The cause of the accident was unclear, Netcare 911 spokesperson Santi Steinmann said."Netcare 911 paramedics, its rescue unit and other services arrived at the scene and found the scene strewn with bricks and building material."Six of the men were seriously injured and another two had moderate injuries. They were treated on scene before being taken to various hospitals for further treatment.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.